    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello,\nI've recently come across an issue in neovim concerning editorconfig behavior.\nAt first I thought it was an issue with the `.editorconfig` file I was using, but apparently (https://github.com/dunglas/symfony-docker/issues/915) it is mostly an issue with neovim.\n\nThe problem I encounter is that `**/Dockerfile` does not match the Dockerfile next to the `.editorconfig` file.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nminimal `.editorconfig` file to reproduce:\n```\nroot = true\n\n[*]\nindent_style = space\n\n[**/{Dockerfile,Caddyfile,*.sh}]\nindent_style = tab\n```\n\nnvim --clean Dockerfile\n:echo b:editorconfig -> {'root': v:true, 'indent_style': 'space'}\n\nnvim --clean foo/Dockerfile\n:echo b:editorconfig -> {'root': v:true, 'indent_style': 'tab'}\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe Dockerfile next to the `.editorconfig` file should be matched against the rule in the file.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.6\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, 9.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux (archlinux)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.26.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\narch repo extra/neovim",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> `**/Dockerfile` does not match the Dockerfile next to the `.editorconfig` file.\n\ni.e. \"sibling to\". It seems that `**/foo` in `.gitignore` matches \"foo\" at the top level, not only subdirectories.  I think some glob libraries don't agree with that, but if editorconfig behaves like that then this does seem to be a bug. \n\ncc @gpanders ",
